  "pages": [
    {
      "page_number": 1,
      "raw_text": "The city council of yesterday decided\nto avail itself of an offer made by\nArthur d. Jones to put water mains\ninto Richland park. because Mr.. Jones\noffered to do the work for 5000 less than\nthe estimated cost made bv the board\nOf public works. Mr.. Jones estimate\nof the cost was not to exceed 5000.\nand the estimate of the board was\n$4,000.\n\n\n1t was decided to let j. d. Sherwood\npay the cost of condemning four lots\nin Houghton & Galatians addition.\nThe lots stood in the way of building\nthe new southeast boulevard, in which\nMr.. Sherwood is deeply interested\nthrough owning real estate."
    }
